'''強姦'''（亦稱強暴、硬幹、姦污、施暴、性侵、強制性交、污辱），是指在沒有得到當事人[[性同意|同意]]的情況下，與之進行[[性交|性交]]等[[插入式性行為|插入式性行為]]，屬[[性侵犯|性侵犯]]的一種。施暴者在過程中可能會用以暴力、[[约制|脅迫]]、[[虐待關係中的權力與控制|濫權]]等手段來迫使對方就範。或以低於法定年齡者、神志不清者、心智疾病患者等無同意能力者為其對象<ref name="who.int">{{cite web |title=Sexual violence chapter 6 |publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]] |date=2002 |access-date=2015-12-05 |url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2002/9241545615_chap6_eng.pdf |archive-date=2008-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080911152633/http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2002/9241545615_chap6_eng.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="dictionary.reference.com">{{cite web |title=Rape |publisher=dictionary.reference.com |date=2011-04-15 |url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/rape |access-date=2019-12-07 |archive-date=2006-08-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060816020425/http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/rape |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="thefreedictionary.com">{{cite web |title=Rape |publisher=legal-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com |date=2011-04-15 |url=http://legal-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/rape |access-date=2019-12-07 |archive-date=2005-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051026001849/http://legal-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/rape |dead-url=no }}</ref>。「強姦」與「性侵犯」有時會代替使用<ref>{{cite book|editor1-last=Petrak |editor1-first=Jenny |editor2-last=Hedge |editor2-first=Barbara |title=The Trauma of Sexual Assault Treatment, Prevention and Practice. |year=2003 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |location=Chichester |isbn=978-0-470-85138-8 |page=2 |url={{Google books |plainurl=yes |id=6KZfQ6cSVHoC |page=2}}}}</ref>。

強姦的報案率、起訴率和定罪率因司法管轄區而異。以國際層面來看，警方所記錄的強姦發生率存有差異——以2008年來計，從每10萬人當中有0.2宗（[[阿塞拜疆|阿塞拜疆]]）至92.9宗（[[波札那|波札那]]）不等；[[中位數|中位數]]則為6.3宗（[[立陶宛|立陶宛]]）<ref name="unodc1">[http://www.unodc.org/documents/data-and-analysis/Crime-statistics/Sexual_violence_sv_against_children_and_rape.xls "Rape at the National Level, number of police recorded offenses".] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unodc.org/documents/data-and-analysis/Crime-statistics/Sexual_violence_sv_against_children_and_rape.xls |date=20131029210321 }} United Nations.</ref>。強姦的施行者大多為男性<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs239/en/ |title=Violence against women |website=World Health Organization |access-date=2017-09-08 |archive-date=2017-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911023744/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs239/en/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。被陌生人強姦的情況一般少於被熟人強姦，[[针对男性的强奸|男對男]]及[[強姦與性別|女對女]]的獄內強姦同樣不屬罕見，但其告發率可能少於其他種類<ref>[[Human_Rights_Watch|Human Rights Watch]][https://www.hrw.org/legacy/reports/2001/prison/report7.html#_1_48 No Escape: Male Rape In U.S. Prisons. Part VII. Anomaly or Epidemic: The Incidence of Prisoner-on-Prisoner Rape.] {{Wayback|url=https://www.hrw.org/legacy/reports/2001/prison/report7.html#_1_48 |date=20140903190935 }}; estimates that 100,000–140,000 violent male-male rapes occur in U.S. prisons annually; compare with [https://www.fbi.gov/ucr/cius2007/offenses/violent_crime/forcible_rape.html FBI statistics] {{Wayback|url=https://www.fbi.gov/ucr/cius2007/offenses/violent_crime/forcible_rape.html |date=20080916010913 }} that estimate 90,000 violent male-female rapes occur annually.</ref><ref>Robert W. Dumond, "Ignominious Victims: Effective Treatment of Male Sexual Assault in Prison," August 15, 1995, p. 2; states that "evidence suggests that [male-male sexual assault in prison] may be a staggering problem". Quoted in {{Cite book |last1=Mariner |first1=Joanne |last2=(Organization) |first2=Human Rights Watch |title=No escape: male rape in U.S. prisons |url={{Google books |plainurl=yes |id=QkFfYfEO5IgC |page=370}} |accessdate=2010-06-07|date=2001-04-17|publisher=Human Rights Watch|isbn=978-1-56432-258-6|page=370}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Struckman-Johnson |first=Cindy |author2=David Struckman-Johnson |year=2006 |title=A Comparison of Sexual Coercion Experiences Reported by Men and Women in Prison |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-interpersonal-violence_2006-12_21_12/page/1591 |journal=Journal of Interpersonal Violence |volume=21 |issue=12 |pages=1591–1615 |issn=0886-2605 |pmid=17065656 |doi=10.1177/0886260506294240}}; reports that "Greater percentages of men (70%) than women (29%) reported that their incident resulted in oral, vaginal, or anal sex. More men (54%) than women (28%) reported an incident that was classified as rape."</ref>。

雖然強姦是個普遍且嚴重的問題，但強姦存有極高的[[黑數|黑數]]，據一些研究，91.6%的強姦都沒有報案，<ref>{{cite web|title=ITALIAN NATIONAL STATISTIC INSTITUTE (ISTAT) SURVEY ON VIOLENCE AGAINST WOMEN, 2006 |url=http://sgdatabase.unwomen.org/searchDetail.action?measureId=26309&baseHREF=country&baseHREFId=675 |website=unwomen.org |publisher=UN WOMEN |accessdate=2016-08-26 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201182537/http://sgdatabase.unwomen.org/searchDetail.action?measureId=26309&baseHREF=country&baseHREFId=675 |archivedate=2014-02-01 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Drug-facilitated, Incapacitated, and Forcible Rape: A National Study|journal=NCJRS|date=February 2007|pages=70|url=https://www.ncjrs.gov/app/publications/abstract.aspx?ID=240972|accessdate=2016-08-26|archive-date=2016-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707023602/https://www.ncjrs.gov/app/publications/abstract.aspx?ID=240972|dead-url=no}}</ref>而在不同地方，人們不向警方通報強姦的理由也各不相同，其中可能的理由包括了害怕遭受報復、不確定犯罪是否發生或侵犯者是否意圖傷害、不希望別人知道自己被強姦的事實、不想要強姦者惹上麻煩、擔心自己反遭受控告（一個可能的因素是一些國家的法律禁止婚前性行為），或對當地的警方的執法有所懷疑等。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Female Victims Of Sexual Violence, 1994-2010|date=2013-03-07|url=http://www.bjs.gov/index.cfm?ty=pbdetail&iid=4594|accessdate=2016-08-26|journal=|archive-date=2020-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917181459/https://www.bjs.gov/index.cfm?ty=pbdetail&iid=4594|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Drug-facilitated, Incapacitated, and Forcible Rape: A National Study|journal=Medical University of South Carolina National Crime Victims Research and Treatment CTR|date=February 2007|pages=70}}</ref>

